              "secondTabOffset": 80,
              "secondTabWidth": 65
            },
            "widgets_values": [
              "first-person view from protagonist's eyes, shooting to lying enemy from sawed-off shotgun, motion blur on arms and hands, simple white t-shirt with blood stains and jeans and fingerless gloves partially visible at screen edges.\n\nenemy is a human-like demon wearing a black leather jacket and jeans, lying on the bloody floor, face had been shot. his dropped gun is near him\n\nenvironment is a interior space: office or mansion or industrial room, believable but subtly broken. perspective is slightly warped, shadows cast in wrong directions, geometry bends inward at the edges.\n\nadditional armed aggressive enemies visible behind the protagonist, out of focus, dangerous. they are shooting to him, but protagonist doesnt feel the pain, he feels euphoria of killing. there's also bloody corpses of enemies in room\n\nthe moment is frozen just before impact, action feels fast and effortless, controlled, purposeful, as if the protagonist is doing something necessary.\n\noverall mood: false clarity, deceptive righteousness, violence perceived as justified but something is deeply wrong.\n\nvisual style: low-poly dirty indie game concept art, sharp pixelated textures, aliased edges, no anti-aliasing, analog noise, grainy film grain, harsh geometry, visible polygon edges.\n\npsychedelic drug trip: acid colors, neon bleeding, chromatic aberration, color shift, warped lighting, but textures remain sharp and pixelated (not blurry, not soft). \n\nthe scene is not chaotic, it is deliberately wrong."
            ]
          },
